{
  "database": {
    "technology": "PostgreSQL 15",
    "models": [
      {
        "name": "User",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "email": "String (Unique, 255 chars)",
          "hashed_password": "String (255 chars)",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)"
        },
        "relations": []
      },
      {
        "name": "Task",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "title": "String (255 chars)",
          "description": "Text (nullable)",
          "status": "Enum('todo', 'in_progress', 'done')",
          "priority": "Enum('low', 'medium', 'high')",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)",
          "updated_at": "DateTime (default now, on update)",
          "user_id": "Integer (Foreign Key -> User.id)"
        },
        "relations": [
          "Many-to-One avec User"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "instructions": "Oumeyma, cr\u00e9e les mod\u00e8les SQLAlchemy avec les champs ci-dessus. Utilise `alembic` pour les migrations. Ajoute des indexes sur `user_id`, `status` et `priority` pour optimiser les filtres. Impl\u00e9mente les relations avec `relationship()` de SQLAlchemy."
  },
  "backend": {
    "technology": "FastAPI + Python 3.10",
    "endpoints": [
      {
        "method": "POST",
        "path": "/auth/register",
        "description": "Inscription utilisateur",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "email": "string",
          "password": "string"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "method": "POST",
        "path": "/auth/login",
        "description": "Connexion utilisateur",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "email": "string",
          "password": "string"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "method": "GET",
        "path": "/tasks",
        "description": "Liste des t\u00e2ches avec filtres",
        "auth_required": true,
        "query_params": {
          "status": "optional enum",
          "priority": "optional enum"
        },
        "response": {
          "tasks": "array of Task"
        }
      },
      {
        "method": "POST",
        "path": "/tasks",
        "description": "Cr\u00e9er une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "string",
          "description": "optional string",
          "status": "enum",
          "priority": "enum"
        },
        "response": {
          "task": "Task"
        }
      },
      {
        "method": "PUT",
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "description": "Modifier une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "optional string",
          "description": "optional string",
          "status": "optional enum",
          "priority": "optional enum"
        },
        "response": {
          "task": "Task"
        }
      },
      {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "description": "Supprimer une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "response": {
          "detail": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "auth": {
      "approach": "JWT avec python-jose (jose) + passlib (bcrypt)",
      "token_expiry": "30 minutes",
      "refresh_tokens": false
    },
    "instructions": "Akram, structure le backend en 3 routers principaux : `/auth`, `/tasks`, et `/users` (pour les infos utilisateur). Utilise `FastAPI Depends` pour l'authentification JWT. Impl\u00e9mente les services `UsersService` et `TasksService` pour la logique m\u00e9tier. Ajoute des validations Pydantic pour les requ\u00eates. Configure CORS pour accepter les requ\u00eates du frontend."
  },
  "frontend": {
    "technology": "React 18 + TypeScript + Vite",
    "components": [
      {
        "name": "AuthProvider",
        "description": "Contexte React pour g\u00e9rer l'authentification (JWT, user data)"
      },
      {
        "name": "LoginForm",
        "description": "Formulaire de connexion avec validation"
      },
      {
        "name": "RegisterForm",
        "description": "Formulaire d'inscription avec validation"
      },
      {
        "name": "Dashboard",
        "description": "Page principale avec liste des t\u00e2ches et filtres"
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskList",
        "description": "Composant affichant les t\u00e2ches avec pagination"
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskForm",
        "description": "Formulaire pour cr\u00e9er/modifier une t\u00e2che"
      },
      {
        "name": "Navbar",
        "description": "Barre de navigation avec bouton de d\u00e9connexion"
      }
    ],
    "pages": [
      {
        "path": "/",
        "component": "Dashboard",
        "protected": true
      },
      {
        "path": "/login",
        "component": "LoginPage",
        "protected": false
      },
      {
        "path": "/register",
        "component": "RegisterPage",
        "protected": false
      }
    ],
    "instructions": "Mactar, utilise React Router v6 pour le routing. Impl\u00e9mente un contexte `AuthProvider` pour g\u00e9rer l'\u00e9tat d'authentification (JWT, user data). Cr\u00e9e des hooks personnalis\u00e9s comme `useAuth()` et `useTasks()`. Utilise `axios` pour les appels API avec un intercepteur pour ajouter le token JWT aux requ\u00eates. Style les composants avec TailwindCSS. Impl\u00e9mente les filtres de statut et priorit\u00e9 avec des dropdowns contr\u00f4l\u00e9s."
  },
  "auth": "JWT avec python-jose + passlib bcrypt (backend), stockage dans localStorage (frontend)",
  "cache": "none",
  "message_broker": "none",
  "container": "Docker + Docker Compose (3 services: frontend, backend, db)",
  "cloud": "D\u00e9ploiement local pour d\u00e9veloppement, cible GitHub Pages (frontend) + Render/Heroku (backend) pour production"
}